-- Heidelberger Druck, Workers Agree on Measures to Cut Costs by $104 Million
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-07-19T14:17:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/heidelberger-druck-workers-agree-on-measures-to-cut-costs-by-104-million.html

          
          
             Heidelberger Druckmaschinen AG and
employee representatives concluded negotiations on cost
reductions, including job cuts and personnel cost savings, the
company said in an e-mailed statement today. Cost reductions of
80 million euros will be achieved in financial year 2011/12, the
company said.  
          
          


  


        